article.description: Kelvin Lewis scored 29 points to lead Houston to a 66-60 victory over SMU Saturday.
article.headline: SMU rallies from 11 back, but then falls short to Houston
article.linkText: SMU's rally against Houston comes up short
article.story: HOUSTON -- Kelvin Lewis scored 29 points to lead Houston to a 66-60 victory over SMU Saturday. Houston led by 11 points early in the second half, but SMU pulled even with just over one minute remaining. Aubrey Coleman made a pair of free throws with a minute left for a 60-58 Cougars lead and Lewis added two more 16 seconds later. Lewis did most of his damage from 3-point range, making 7-of-16 from behind the arc. Coleman added 16 points for Houston (13-11, 5-5 Conference USA). Derek Williams had 24 points to lead SMU (11-13, 4-6). Mouhammad Faye had 10 and Papa Dia just missed a double-double with nine points and 10 rebounds. Even with Lewis' 50 percent shooting day (9-for-18), the Cougars struggled from outside, making just 32 percent of their shots. But Houston was 18-for-20 from the free-throw line, including the last eight in the final minute.
